<script type='text/template' id='registrationTemplate'>

  <section class="main-content border-btm-grey small-padding shadow-off" style="background-color: #3962ae;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
      	<div class="col-md-12">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
      			  <div class="special-heading textalignleft default lighter animated-content move_right animate" style="padding-bottom: 0px;">
      			    <h1 style="color: #ffffff;" class="fancy default"><span>Register</span></h1>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="main-content default-padding shadow-off">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
              <div class="special-heading textalignleft default" style="padding-bottom: 10px;">
                <h2 class="fancy default"><span>1. Start donating compute time</span></h2>
              </div>
              <div class="special-heading textalignleft default" style="padding-bottom: 30px;">
                <h6 class="fancy default"><span>In order to start donating compute power, you’ll need to register for World Community Grid, and then download software called BOINC manager.</span></h6>
              </div>
              <div class="special-heading textalignleft default" style="padding-bottom: 0px;">
                <h3 class="fancy default"><span>Instructions</span></h3>
              </div>
              <div class="text-block">
                <ol>
                  <li>Register for the <a title="worldcommunitygrid.org/reg/viewRegister.do" href="http://www.worldcommunitygrid.org/reg/viewRegister.do" target="_blank">World Community Grid</a>.</li>
                  <li>Select projects you’d like to participate in (we recommend selecting all – why not?).</li>
                  <li>Download the BOINC Manager software. Berkeley researchers developed BOINC Manager as a way for computers around the world to volunteer computing time in a secure and efficient way. In order to receive points, it’s very important you join World Community Grid project. Detailed instructions are here:
                    <ul>
                      <li><a title="worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/installInstMac.jsp" href="https://secure.worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/installInstMac.jsp" target="_blank">Mac instructions</a></li>
                      <li><a title="worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/installInstWin.jsp" href="https://secure.worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/installInstWin.jsp" target="_blank">Windows instructions</a></li>
                      <li><a title="worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/installInstAndroid.jsp" href="https://secure.worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/installInstAndroid.jsp" target="_blank">Android instructions</a></li>
                      <li><a title="worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/installInstLinux.jsp" href="https://secure.worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/installInstLinux.jsp" target="_blank">Linux instructions</a></li>
                    </ul>
                  </li>
                  <li><a href="http://www.worldcommunitygrid.org/team/viewTeamInfo.do?teamId=0QGNJ4D832" target="_blank">Join the Ripple Labs team</a>.</li> You must remain a member of the Ripple Labs team to claim XRP.
                  <li>You’re now set up to start donating! Run the BOINC Manager program each time you want to donate.</li>
                  <li>Now that you’ve started donating, you may want to change your settings so your computer will donate the max amount possible.
                    <ul>
                      <li>Change your device settings on World Community Grid to “maximum output” <a title="worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/device/viewProfiles.do" href="https://secure.worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/device/viewProfiles.do" target="_blank">here</a>.</li>
                      <li>In Boincmanager, go to Advanced &gt; Preferences. You can change your settings so you’re donating compute time while the computer is in use, on batteries etc.</li>
                    </ul>
                  </li>
                  <li>Need more help? The <a href="https://secure.worldcommunitygrid.org/help/viewHelp.do" target="_blank">WCG help center</a> has great tutorial videos, and you can visit the <a href="https://secure.worldcommunitygrid.org/forums/wcg/index" target="_blank">WCG forum</a>.</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
          	</div>
          </div>
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
              <div class="divider normal animated-content fade_in animate" style="margin-top: 60px; margin-bottom: 72px;"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
              <div class="special-heading textalignleft default animated-content fade_in animate" style="padding-bottom: 10px;">
                <h2 class="fancy default"><span>2. Start Claiming XRP</span></h2>
              </div>
              <div class="special-heading textalignleft default animated-content fade_in animate" style="padding-bottom: 0px;">
                <h3 class="fancy default"><span>Connect your WCG account to your Ripple account</span></h3>
              </div>
              <div class="text-block animated-content fade_in animate">
                <p class="regform_p">Once you start claiming XRP, all your compute time associated with your WCG username will be deposited into your Ripple public address. You will not be able to un-link these two accounts. We issue XRP once a day. Please wait 24 hours and then check your balance.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="blank_divider" style="height: 5px;"></div>
              <form method='post' action='/api/users' id='newUserForm'>
              	<div class="wpb_raw_code wpb_content_element wpb_raw_html">
              		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
              			<p>
                      Ripple Public Address
                      <br>
                      <input type="text" name="ripple_address" value="" size="40" aria-required="true">
                    </p>
                    <p class='errors' id='rippleAddressErrors'>Please enter a valid ripple public address</p>
                      <div class="text-block animated-content fade_in animate">
                        <p class="regform_p" style="font-size: 12px;">To find your public address, <a title="https://ripple.com/client" href="https://ripple.com/client" target="_blank">login to</a> or <a title="https://ripple.com/client/#/register" href="https://ripple.com/client/#/register" target="_blank">create</a> a Ripple account. Click on the “Receive” icon and copy your public address. Only enter addresses for which you have control.</p>
                      </div>
                    <p>
                      WCG Username
                      <br>
                      <input type="text" name="username" size="40" aria-required="true">
                    </p>
                    <p class='errors' id='wcgUsernameErrors'></p>
                    <p>
                      WCG Verification Code
                      <br>
                      <input type="text" name="verification_code" value="" size="40" aria-required="true">
                    </p>
                    <p class='errors' id='wcgVerificationCodeErrors'></p>
                    <div class="text-block animated-content fade_in animate">
                      <p class="regform_p" style="font-size: 12px;"><a title="https://secure.worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/viewMyProfile.do" href="https://secure.worldcommunitygrid.org/ms/viewMyProfile.do" target="_blank">Login to your WCG profile</a>&nbsp;to find&nbsp;your verification code.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
              	</div>
              	<div class="blank_divider" style="height: 15px;"></div>
                <input type='submit' class="button-main button-large animated-content fade_in animate" value="Start Claiming XRP">
                  <img class='ajaxLoader' src='/ajax-loader.gif' style='display:none'/>
                </input>
              </div>
            </form>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="main-content no-padding shadow-off">
    <div class="container-fluid">
